  "prompt": "Why did Ian Mckellen have emotional breakdowns when on set on the Hobbit?",
  "response": "Ian McKellen experienced emotional breakdowns on the set of \"The Hobbit\" primarily due to the isolation and technical challenges associated with filming the movie. The production used a significant amount of green screen and other visual effects to create the fantastical world of Middle-earth. This required McKellen to act alone in front of green screens or with stand-ins rather than interacting directly with other actors. \n\nMcKellen, who is a seasoned stage actor and thrives on the camaraderie and direct interaction with fellow performers, found this process to be quite distressing. At one point during filming, he reportedly exclaimed, \"This is not why I became an actor.\" The emotional toll was considerable, as the environment was vastly different from the traditional stage or film sets he was accustomed to.",
